# Lumina Multi-Tenancy Patterns

## Overview

Lumina provides built-in multi-tenancy through organization scoping. Every API request is scoped to an organization, and models define how they relate to the organization.

## Direct Ownership: BelongsToOrganization Trait

For models with a direct `organization_id` foreign key column, use the `BelongsToOrganization` trait:

```php
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\HasFactory;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\SoftDeletes;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HasValidation;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HidableColumns;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\BelongsToOrganization;

class Project extends \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    use SoftDeletes;
    use HasValidation;
    use HidableColumns;
    use BelongsToOrganization;

    protected $fillable = [
        'name',
        'description',
        'organization_id',
    ];

    public function organization()
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(Organization::class);
    }
}
```

The `BelongsToOrganization` trait automatically:
- Scopes all queries to the current organization
- Sets `organization_id` on creation
- Validates that the record belongs to the resolved organization

## Indirect Ownership: Auto-Detected from BelongsTo

For models that belong to an organization through another model (no direct `organization_id`), Lumina auto-detects the ownership path by introspecting BelongsTo relationships:

```php
<?php

namespace App\Models;

use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Factories\HasFactory;
use Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\SoftDeletes;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HasValidation;
use Lumina\LaravelApi\Traits\HidableColumns;

class Task extends \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    use SoftDeletes;
    use HasValidation;
    use HidableColumns;

    // Task -> Project -> Organization is auto-detected via BelongsTo
    protected $fillable = [
        'title',
        'description',
        'project_id',
    ];

    public function project()
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(Project::class);
    }
}
```

```php
class Comment extends \Illuminate\Database\Eloquent\Model
{
    use HasFactory;
    use SoftDeletes;
    use HasValidation;
    use HidableColumns;

    // Comment -> Article -> Organization is auto-detected via BelongsTo
    protected $fillable = ['body', 'article_id', 'user_id'];

    public function article()
    {
        return $this->belongsTo(Article::class);
    }
}
```

Lumina walks the `belongsTo` chain automatically to find the organization.

## Route Strategies

### Prefix Strategy (default)

The organization identifier is a route prefix:

```
GET /api/{org}/projects
GET /api/acme-corp/projects
```

Configuration:

```php
// config/lumina.php
'organization' => [
    'model' => \App\Models\Organization::class,
    'identifier' => 'slug',
    'route_strategy' => 'prefix',
],
```

Middleware used: `ResolveOrganizationFromRoute`

### Subdomain Strategy

The organization identifier is a subdomain:

```
GET https://acme-corp.api.example.com/projects
```

Configuration:

```php
// config/lumina.php
'organization' => [
    'model' => \App\Models\Organization::class,
    'identifier' => 'slug',
    'route_strategy' => 'subdomain',
    'domain' => 'api.example.com',
],
```

Middleware used: `ResolveOrganizationFromSubdomain`

## Organization Identifier Options

The `identifier` config determines which column is used in the URL to identify the organization:

| Identifier | URL Example                     | Column Used |
|------------|---------------------------------|-------------|
| `id`       | `/api/1/projects`               | `id`        |
| `slug`     | `/api/acme-corp/projects`       | `slug`      |
| `uuid`     | `/api/550e8400-.../projects`    | `uuid`      |

```php
'organization' => [
    'identifier' => 'slug', // 'id', 'slug', or 'uuid'
],
```

## Full Configuration Example

```php
<?php

// config/lumina.php
return [
    'models' => [
        \App\Models\User::class,
        \App\Models\Project::class,
        \App\Models\Task::class,
        \App\Models\Article::class,
        \App\Models\Comment::class,
    ],

    'organization' => [
        'model' => \App\Models\Organization::class,
        'identifier' => 'slug',
        'route_strategy' => 'prefix',
    ],

    'auth' => [
        'middleware' => ['auth:sanctum'],
        'guard' => 'sanctum',
    ],

    'prefix' => 'api',

    'soft_deletes' => [
        'enabled' => true,
        'routes' => true, // Generates trash/restore/force-delete routes
    ],
];
```

## Middleware

Lumina provides two middleware classes for resolving the organization from the request:

### ResolveOrganizationFromRoute

Used with the `prefix` strategy. Extracts the organization identifier from the route parameter:

```php
// Automatically applied by Lumina when route_strategy is 'prefix'
// Resolves {org} from /api/{org}/resource
```

### ResolveOrganizationFromSubdomain

Used with the `subdomain` strategy. Extracts the organization identifier from the request host:

```php
// Automatically applied by Lumina when route_strategy is 'subdomain'
// Resolves org from {org}.api.example.com
```

Both middleware classes resolve the organization and make it available via:

```php
// Access the current organization anywhere in the application
$organization = app('lumina.organization');

// Or via the helper
$organization = lumina_organization();
```

## DON'Ts

- **DO NOT** manually filter by organization in queries. The `BelongsToOrganization` trait and auto-detected BelongsTo chains handle organization scoping automatically.

```php
// BAD: Manual organization filtering
$projects = Project::where('organization_id', $orgId)->get();

// GOOD: Lumina handles it automatically
$projects = Project::all(); // Already scoped to current org
```
